ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W2_LostItemControlCenter

Class Name: LostItemControlCenter

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 83 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a lost item management system for a school office.
The program should register lost items, prevent duplicate item IDs,
search by category, process claim requests, and count claim attempts.

Requirements
- Use ArrayList<LostItem> to store all lost items.
- Use HashSet<String> to prevent duplicate item IDs.
- Use HashSet<String> to manage existing categories.
- Use HashMap<String, Integer> to count claim attempts by student.
- Process claim requests using item ID, claimed state, and description matching.

Learning Objective
Practice Java Collection Framework in an object-oriented program.
Focus on choosing the right collection for each responsibility and connecting
multiple classes through method calls.